# No Hardcoded User-Facing Strings

All visible text in frontend components MUST use `t("key")` from `react-i18next`. Never hardcode strings directly in JSX.

## What counts as user-facing text

- Labels, titles, descriptions, placeholders, tooltips, button text, tab labels, error/success messages, table headers, badges, banners

## What is exempt

- `aria-*` attributes that duplicate a translated visible label
- CSS class names, test IDs, `key` props, enum values, URLs
- Numbers, punctuation-only strings, format patterns (e.g. `"-"`, `"/"`)
- Developer-facing strings (console.log, error codes)

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — hardcoded strings
<Text>Prize</Text>
<Text>Participants</Text>
<Button>Join Challenge</Button>

// ✅ GOOD — translated
<Text>{t("Prize")}</Text>
<Text>{t("Participants")}</Text>
<Button>{t("Join Challenge")}</Button>
```

## When adding new translated strings

Follow the `translate.mdc` rule: add the key to `en.json` and all 14 other language files, sorted alphabetically.
